<item>
            <title>[SYNAPSE-57] Synapse Send mediator should not stop mediation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SYNAPSE-57</link>
                <project id="12310201" key="SYNAPSE">Synapse</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It should be possible to perform a &amp;lt;send/&amp;gt; and continue mediation. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If a response message has already been sent over a transport such as http, and another is being attempted, this is a user error and the second should fail. However, is using a transport such as JMS/mail, it should be possible to send the same message out multiple times, as well as continue processing after a send operation. e.g. in the case of a one-way message&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
